    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "This factor assesses whether validation activities were conducted in a context sufficiently close to the intended COU to support credibility transfer. In COU1, the validation activity IS the COU: the FEA model is being validated directly against the ASTM F1717 bench test that constitutes the regulatory submission test. There is no gap between the validation context and the use context because they are identical by construction — the model is not being applied to a different geometry, loading scenario, or patient population beyond what was tested. Applying this factor would require comparing the validation context to itself, which is logically vacuous. This factor is therefore not applicable to COU1 and would only become relevant in a COU2 scenario where the validated model is extrapolated to a design variant or loading condition not directly tested."
